The paper proposes a nonlinear model for high-order data classification, which involves the use of tensors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a feedforward neural network (FNN) and a new learning algorithm, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on third-order hyperspectral data, which suggests that it may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
